{"TopicId":220620,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"No mouse scrolling =\u003E No way to play KSP 2 ?","CreatedByName":"Sans","CreatedById":214540,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-04T00:01:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sans","CreatedById":214540,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-04T00:01:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs the title said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are no keybinds for zooming.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChrisShourai","CreatedById":226083,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-04T20:05:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s the reason you do not have/use a mouse scroll wheel, is it an accessibility issue?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sans","CreatedById":214540,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-05T11:56:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224336871\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221699128318\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226083\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ChrisShourai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, ChrisShourai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s the reason you do not have/use a mouse scroll wheel, is it an accessibility issue?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmy mouse is broken and I can\u0027t buy a new one right now. I was using \u002B and - to zoom on KSP 1 and it did the job. But these keybinds aren\u0027t there yet on KSP 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-05T12:16:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/214540-sans/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022214540\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/214540-sans/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sans\u003C/a\u003E, your issue has been moved from KSP 2 Discussions to KSP 2 Suggestions and Development for better visibility.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChrisShourai","CreatedById":226083,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-05T18:30:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/214540-sans/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022214540\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/214540-sans/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sans\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Try this. It\u0027s a temp solution. I\u0027m sure the game will have more accessibility options on full release.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ETo access mouse settings, select the\u00A0\u003Cb\u003EStart\u00A0\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0button, then select\u00A0\u003Cb\u003ESettings\u00A0\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0\u0026gt;\u00A0\u003Cb\u003EEase of Access\u00A0\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0\u0026gt;\u00A0\u003Cb\u003EMouse\u00A0\u003C/b\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#363636;font-size:1.6em;\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022font-size:1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#1e1e1e;font-size:1em;padding:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ETurn on the toggle under\u003Cb\u003E\u00A0Control your mouse with a keypad\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0if you want to control your mouse using a numeric keypad.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022font-size:1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#1e1e1e;font-size:1em;padding:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ESelect\u00A0\u003Cb\u003EChange other mouse options\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0to change your primary mouse button, set scrolling options, and more.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022font-size:1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#1e1e1e;font-size:1em;padding:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EIf you want your pointer to display a trail across the screen when you move it, select\u00A0\u003Cb\u003EAdditional mouse options\u003C/b\u003E, and check the box next to\u00A0\u003Cb\u003EDisplay pointer trails\u00A0\u003C/b\u003Eon the\u00A0\u003Cb\u003EPointer Options\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0tab.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#1e1e1e;font-size:1em;padding:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#1e1e1e;font-size:1em;padding:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EFound here:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/make-your-mouse-keyboard-and-other-input-devices-easier-to-use-10733da7-fa82-88be-0672-f123d4b3dcfe#:~:text=Control%20your%20mouse%20with%20a,on%20the%20Mouse%20keys%20switch.\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/make-your-mouse-keyboard-and-other-input-devices-easier-to-use-10733da7-fa82-88be-0672-f123d4b3dcfe#:~:text=Control your mouse with a,on the Mouse keys switch.\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}